6:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Rate Mechanics"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo calculates funding rates hourly using its rollup-based price discovery, providing more frequent rate adjustments but potentially higher volatility. Phemex uses traditional 8-hour intervals with centralized rate calculation, offering more predictable funding schedules. Aevo's DEX model creates funding rates through on-chain settlement mechanisms, while Phemex relies on centralized order matching with faster execution. The hourly vs 8-hour difference significantly impacts arbitrage timing and capital efficiency strategies."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lb",null,{"items":[{"question":"Which exchange offers better funding rate arbitrage opportunities?","answer":"Phemex typically offers more consistent arbitrage opportunities due to its 8-hour funding cycles and lower maker fees. Aevo's hourly rates create more frequent opportunities but require faster execution and deeper understanding of rollup mechanics."},{"question":"How do the settlement mechanisms affect arbitrage execution?","answer":"Aevo's on-chain settlement provides transparency but may have slower finality during network congestion. Phemex's centralized settlement offers faster execution speeds and immediate position updates, crucial for high-frequency arbitrage strategies."},{"question":"What are the liquidity differences for funding rate arbitrage?","answer":"Phemex generally provides better liquidity depth for major pairs, while Aevo's smaller liquidity pools may cause slippage on larger arbitrage positions. However, Aevo offers unique pre-launch markets not available on Phemex."},{"question":"Which platform has lower total costs for arbitrage trading?","answer":"Phemex has lower maker fees (0.01% vs 0.02%) making it more cost-effective for high-frequency arbitrage. However, Aevo's combined options and perps platform may offer cross-product arbitrage opportunities that offset higher individual trading costs."}]}]
